OOC: People are complaining nothing new is happening
so the rpg is dieing.  I have an idea for something
new that wouldn't be another farfetched idea, the
problem is it involves sacrificing a Maximal, and
would mainly be a momentary moral boost and intersting
plot complication rather than a long term improvement.

BIC:  Sunhawk gets up and walks to Talos's office.

Sunhawk:  What do you want me to do, SIR!

--- Jonathan <jhogan@...> wrote:
> ::Hot Rod::Hot Rod realized that he had been talking
> a long time and it had turned into a speech more
> then just conversation, so he stoped.
> 
> {Nightshade}
> 
>     Nightshade chuckled shaking her head, "Same old
> Hot Rod, out to save the universe even if that
> universe is a completely out of whack system."
> Grinning she shrugged, "I tried the whole peaceful
> protest to the downgrade, it didn't work. I assure
> you I didn't go predicon because it didn't work, no
> I tried rallying under the Autobot flag again and
> found most agreeing with the council. I was declared
> rogue and lumped alongside the predicons."
> 
>    Sighing she shrugged sitting back on her cot
> looking at the bot before her, "When Megatron busted
> out of the security detachment on that station and
> needed a crew I signed on only cause it was my only
> way off that station that didn't involve my spark
> being extracted to be stored in the criminal
> division of cybertrons libraries like the
> combaticons. I couldn't continue my fight without a
> body so I opted for the only chance I had."
> 
>     "It wasn't the prettiest choice but it was the
> better of two evils."
> 
> 
>
